📌 Image Performance Cheatsheet

- ✅ Image Size: <= 300KB for hero/LCP images
- ✅ Format: WebP or AVIF > JPG > PNG
- ✅ Dimensions: 768px (mobile), 1200px+ (desktop)
- ✅ Test on: Fast 4G or Fast 3G, cache disabled
- ✅ Use width/height to avoid CLS
- ✅ Reduce hydration delay in React for faster LCP
- ✅ Use CDN with cache headers for faster delivery
- ✅ Use Next.js <Image /> component for auto optimization
- ✅ Use `<picture>` and `srcset` for responsive images

------------------------------step 1------------------------------ 
step 1 by adding only height, width and loading:- lazy or eager and reducing img size by 300k

/**
 * 🧠 Image Optimization Summary (Practical Case Study)
 *
 * 🔍 Initial Setup:
 * - Image: 4MB JPG (imported directly)
 * - No width/height defined
 * - No compression or optimization
 *
 * 📉 Initial Performance:
 * - LCP: 6.4s ❌ (very poor)
 * - CLS: 0.81 ❌ (layout shift)
 *
 * ✅ Step 1: Added width & height attributes
 * - LCP improved to 1.79s
 * - CLS dropped to 0.03 ✅
 *
 * ⚠️ Step 2: Converted to WebP (1.2MB)
 * - LCP degraded to 3.54s (still large file)
 * - CLS stayed stable
 *
 * ✅ Step 2.5: Compressed WebP to 218KB
 * - Final LCP: 2.22s 🟢 (Good performance)
 * - CLS: 0.03 ✅
 *
 * 📌 Lessons:
 * - Add explicit width & height to prevent layout shift (CLS)
 * - Compress & convert large images to WebP/AVIF for LCP
 * - Keep hero/banner images under ~300KB for best results
 */

------------------------------step 2------------------------------ 
Compress & convert images to modern formats (WebP/AVIF) and resize properly

/**
 * - Convert JPG/PNG → WebP or AVIF for smaller file size
 * - Use tools: Squoosh, TinyPNG, or CLI libraries like sharp
 * - Resize images according to max display size (e.g., 1200px desktop)
 * - Compress images further to reduce bytes (target <=300KB)
 * - Test impact on LCP and CLS after compression
 */

------------------------------step 3------------------------------ 
Use `<picture>` and `srcset` for responsive images

/**
 * - Use `<picture>` element to provide multiple image sources/formats:
 *    ```jsx
 *    <picture>
 *      <source srcSet="image.webp" type="image/webp" />
 *      <source srcSet="image.jpg" type="image/jpeg" />
 *      <img src="image.jpg" alt="description" width="1200" height="800" loading="lazy" />
 *    </picture>
 *    ```
 * - Use `srcset` attribute on `<img>` to serve images for different viewport sizes:
 *    ```html
 *    <img 
 *      src="image-1200.jpg" 
 *      srcset="image-600.jpg 600w, image-1200.jpg 1200w" 
 *      sizes="(max-width: 600px) 600px, 1200px" 
 *      alt="desc" width="1200" height="800" loading="lazy" 
 *    />
 *    ```
 * - This reduces data usage on smaller devices and improves LCP
 */

------------------------------step 4------------------------------ 
Lazy Loading, Priority, and Decoding in Next.js or React

/**
 * - Use lazy loading (`loading="lazy"`) for below-the-fold images
 * - For hero/LCP images, set `priority` prop in Next.js <Image />
 * - Next.js sets decoding="async" by default for better painting
 * - Avoid blocking the main thread by async decoding images
 */

------------------------------step 5------------------------------ 
CDN Delivery and Cache Control Headers

/**
 * - Serve images via CDN (Vercel, Cloudflare, AWS CloudFront)
 * - Set HTTP Cache-Control headers: `public, max-age=31536000, immutable`
 * - This ensures fast delivery globally and browser caching
 * - Preload critical LCP images to improve perceived load speed
 */

------------------------------step 6------------------------------ 
Next.js `<Image />` Benefits & Usage

/**
 * - Requires explicit width & height to prevent CLS
 * - Automatically optimizes image formats & sizes per device
 * - Lazy loads images by default except for those with `priority`
 * - Integrates with Vercel Edge CDN for fast global delivery
 * - Handles responsive images with srcSet & sizes internally
 * - Allows external image domains via next.config.js configuration
 */

------------------------------bonus------------------------------ 
Other Important Notes

/**
 * - Test on slow network (Fast 3G or throttled Fast 4G), and no cache
 * - Use Lighthouse or WebPageTest to measure LCP, CLS, and FID
 * - Hydration delay affects LCP in React; minimize JS bundle size & improve SSR
 * - Provide meaningful alt text for accessibility & SEO
 * - Avoid layout shift by reserving space and avoid injecting content late
 */
